1
00:00:21,522 --> 00:00:22,523
<i>Have you heard from Ace?</i>

2
00:00:22,606 --> 00:00:23,983
- <i>Not yet. What about Gem?</i>
- <i>No.</i>

3
00:00:24,066 --> 00:00:25,443
- Where's Teo?
- <i>Who are you?</i>

4
00:00:25,526 --> 00:00:26,902
<i>Is he the one</i>
<i>you're looking for, ma'am?</i>

5
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:28,738
<i>Why did we get the cops involved?</i>

6
00:00:28,821 --> 00:00:29,697
<i>Why don't we just pay</i>

7
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:30,948
<i>- the ransom?</i>
- <i>No, Katarina.</i>

8
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:32,199
<i>When this happened to Ace before,</i>

9
00:00:32,283 --> 00:00:33,117
we did not involve the police.

10
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,243
I refuse to make the same mistake again.

11
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:36,078
I'm sorry, Judge, but I really don't know.

12
00:00:36,162 --> 00:00:37,663
I've seen a hundred cases like this.

13
00:00:37,747 --> 00:00:39,206
<i>It's often an inside job.</i>

14
00:00:39,290 --> 00:00:41,125
<i>I will find out if you're lying, Teo.</i>

15
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:43,544
- <i>Do you have my 20 million?</i>
- <i>When and where?</i>

16
00:00:43,627 --> 00:00:45,004
<i>At the end of Sunset Drive in Bulacan.</i>

17
00:00:45,087 --> 00:00:46,964
<i>We'll have units on standby there.</i>

18
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:48,215
<i>No big movements.</i>

19
00:00:48,299 --> 00:00:50,134
Your priority is my son.

20
00:00:50,217 --> 00:00:52,136
<i>I don't care whoever gets left behind.</i>

21
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:53,679
<i>Is that clear?</i>

22
00:01:00,311 --> 00:01:01,228
Damn it!

23
00:01:01,312 --> 00:01:04,899
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

24
00:01:32,551 --> 00:01:34,553
There's nothing we can do, bro.

25
00:01:35,095 --> 00:01:37,014
The Veronas got Gem back.

26
00:01:38,224 --> 00:01:41,018
But the good news is
they didn't get the money.

27
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,812
I learned my lesson in Morocco,

28
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:45,314
so I made sure to stash it.

29
00:01:45,397 --> 00:01:46,941
Are you sure they won't find it?

30
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:47,942
Yes.

31
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:52,404
They can tear the place apart,
but they won't find the money.

32
00:01:53,239 --> 00:01:54,156
Okay.

33
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,866
Let's go back for it another time.

34
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:57,451
They're still checking the place.

35
00:01:58,452 --> 00:01:59,328
And Gem is...

36
00:02:02,206 --> 00:02:03,415
...still with them.

37
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:05,876
Let's lay low for now.

38
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:08,420
We'll figure out how to get Gem back.

39
00:02:33,195 --> 00:02:34,238


40
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:38,659
They took me somewhere.

41
00:02:41,245 --> 00:02:43,372
Then they blindfolded me.

42
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:46,834
It was dark.

43
00:02:49,545 --> 00:02:52,214
I don't know how many days I was there.

44
00:02:52,756 --> 00:02:55,009
I was in some kind of container van.

45
00:02:56,302 --> 00:02:58,554
Then they brought me out.

46
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:02,558
And then I heard them talking.

47
00:03:05,019 --> 00:03:06,979
They said they were going to sell me...

48
00:03:08,898 --> 00:03:09,982
traffic me.

49
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,027
Then a fight broke out.

50
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:16,989
They were arguing over money.

51
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:18,240
Then...

52
00:03:19,283 --> 00:03:21,410
I heard a gunshot.

53
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:22,578
So I ran.

54
00:03:23,412 --> 00:03:26,498
I was so scared.

55
00:03:26,582 --> 00:03:28,208
Someone grabbed me.

56
00:03:28,292 --> 00:03:31,921

They told me to go with them.

57
00:03:32,588 --> 00:03:35,007
I didn't know
if they were one of the kidnappers

58
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,800
or someone trying to help me.

59
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:39,219
So I didn't stop.

60
00:03:39,303 --> 00:03:42,473
I kept running and...

61
00:03:43,349 --> 00:03:45,225
...the next thing I knew,

62
00:03:48,062 --> 00:03:49,480
I was shot.

63
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:52,608
That's not
what you were wearing when I last saw you.

64
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:55,319


65
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:56,654
Oh, my goodness.

66
00:03:57,863 --> 00:03:59,698
Did they assault you?

67
00:04:00,783 --> 00:04:01,825
No, Mama.

68
00:04:02,493 --> 00:04:05,287

They just made me change clothes.

69
00:04:06,497 --> 00:04:08,123
But they didn't hurt me.

70
00:04:12,086 --> 00:04:14,463
You're safe now. You're home.

71
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:18,175
I will not allow anyone
to ever hurt you again.

72
00:04:32,189 --> 00:04:33,273
Oh.

73
00:04:33,357 --> 00:04:34,525
Is your brother not inside?

74
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:35,901
Nope.

75
00:04:36,485 --> 00:04:37,903
Where could he be?

76
00:04:37,987 --> 00:04:38,821
- Pa?
Huh?

77
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:40,489
Ronnie, have you seen this?

78
00:04:42,366 --> 00:04:45,744
<i>Controversial lawyer Ace Verona</i>
<i>and his wife, Gem Verona,</i>

79
00:04:45,828 --> 00:04:47,997
<i>have been rescued.</i>

80
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:50,791
<i>Both hostages are safe.</i>

81
00:04:50,874 --> 00:04:54,169
<i>Authorities are still searching</i>
<i>for those responsible.</i>

82
00:04:54,253 --> 00:04:55,713
Does Teo know about this?

83
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:00,676
Where is he?

84
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:03,095
Ronnie, did you not notice him?

85
00:05:03,178 --> 00:05:05,472
You were the last one
to come home last night.

86
00:05:05,556 --> 00:05:06,807
- Pa.
Oh.

87
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,600
There you are. Where were you?

88
00:05:09,768 --> 00:05:11,061
I went for a walk.

89
00:05:11,145 --> 00:05:12,312
Have you heard?

90
00:05:12,396 --> 00:05:13,522
What?

91
00:05:13,605 --> 00:05:16,734
Sir Ace and Ma'am Gem have been found.

92
00:05:17,443 --> 00:05:18,944
Really? When?

93
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:20,446
Well, last night.

94
00:05:20,529 --> 00:05:23,115
The family must've paid off the ransom.

95
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:25,451
I heard it was 40 million.

96
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:28,454
Forty million is nothing to them.

97
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,290
That family has the ability
to make that kind of money,

98
00:05:31,373 --> 00:05:32,833
legally or not.

99
00:05:36,378 --> 00:05:40,424
It's like danger always finds its way
to the Veronas.

100
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,844
Maybe it's best
if we stop working for them.

101
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:45,888
Not yet, son.

102
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:48,640
It would be embarrassing to leave them.

103
00:05:48,724 --> 00:05:50,100
I still owe Judge Divino.

104
00:05:50,184 --> 00:05:53,020
Then you'll be working
for them forever, bro.

105
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:55,314
Jeez, Ronnie.

106
00:05:55,397 --> 00:05:57,316
We just need to stay for at least a year.

107
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,276
You love your job, huh, Papa?

108
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:01,278
You won't leave those rich folks.

109
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:04,364
- Here, Mr. Alonzo.
Mm. You got that right.

110
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:07,659
Mm-hmm.

111
00:06:07,743 --> 00:06:09,161
The shipment was hit
with substantial losses

112
00:06:09,244 --> 00:06:11,330
due to Ordoñez's actions.

113
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:16,919
The kidnapping also caused our family

114
00:06:18,003 --> 00:06:20,672
a financial loss of 40 million.

115
00:06:20,756 --> 00:06:23,675
<i>It's a good thing</i>
<i>Ace is safe, right, Divino?</i>

116
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:24,843
Yes.

117
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,638

But he still can't handle the assignment.

118
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:29,932
So I'm taking over.

119
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:33,352

But in spite of the kidnapping of my son

120
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:35,187

and the problem with Ordoñez,

121
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:39,233
our Myanmar shipment
will proceed as scheduled.

122
00:06:39,316 --> 00:06:40,901
Manila to Bangkok,

123
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:42,778
land travel to Yangon.

124
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:45,489
We'll bounce back from this.

125
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:48,200
Thanks to Pearl,

126
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:51,328
we haven't lost the trust of our partners.

127
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:56,834
Thank you for always fixing our problems.

128
00:07:02,297 --> 00:07:04,800


129
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:17,521
Don't look at me like that.

130
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:18,981
I'll be fine.

131
00:07:19,064 --> 00:07:21,108
Boss knows what happened.

132
00:07:22,109 --> 00:07:23,277
He's worried about you.

133
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:25,779
Tell him I'm okay.

134
00:07:25,863 --> 00:07:26,989
Still alive and kicking.

135
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,705
It's Teo.

136
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:36,790
Hello?

137
00:07:36,874 --> 00:07:38,667
I'm so sorry, Gem.

138
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,752
I wasn't able to get you out.

139
00:07:40,836 --> 00:07:42,296
<i>Don't blame yourself.</i>

140
00:07:42,379 --> 00:07:44,256
You did everything you could.

141
00:07:44,339 --> 00:07:47,092
Just sit tight.
I'm getting you out of there.

142
00:07:47,551 --> 00:07:49,636
Just stay put, Teo.

143
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:52,389
You and your father are in danger.

144
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,099
You work for the Veronas.

145
00:07:54,183 --> 00:07:55,809
We're not giving up.

146
00:07:55,893 --> 00:07:59,354
I have the money.
We'll use it so you can escape.

147
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:00,856
Thank you.

148
00:08:02,274 --> 00:08:03,442
I'll be counting on that.

149
00:08:03,525 --> 00:08:05,527
But let's wait for the right time.

150
00:08:06,195 --> 00:08:07,404
Be careful.

151
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:09,198
You too.

152
00:08:22,252 --> 00:08:23,420
Mm!

153
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:26,548
My God, Ace,
I'm so glad you're here now.

154
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:28,967
I was worried sick.

155
00:08:29,051 --> 00:08:29,968
Your big bro's tough.

156
00:08:30,052 --> 00:08:31,970
We're Veronas, remember?

157
00:08:32,054 --> 00:08:34,348
- We can handle anything.
- Yep.

158
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,725
Well, rest now, my son.

159
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:39,937
Dr. Collado
will be here tomorrow for your therapy.

160
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:41,396
I don't need it. Where's Teo?

161
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:42,856
He won't be reporting for work.

162
00:08:43,899 --> 00:08:45,901
Ever since he arrived,

163
00:08:45,984 --> 00:08:47,778
it's been one problem after another.

164
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:50,405
I'm beginning to think he's the reason.

165
00:08:50,489 --> 00:08:52,658
If that's true, he should be in jail.

166
00:08:52,741 --> 00:08:54,826
- Do you have any proof?
- None.

167
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:56,620
Yet.

168
00:08:56,703 --> 00:08:59,373
But during the time I served as a judge,

169
00:08:59,456 --> 00:09:02,042
I have met a lot of liars
who already look guilty

170
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:03,669
even before they confess.

171
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:05,128
Of course, if you think he's responsible,

172
00:09:05,212 --> 00:09:07,089
then we need to keep him close.

173
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,632
So we can keep an eye on him.

174
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:11,468
And if you're wrong,
then we have nothing to lose, right?

175
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,470
Yeah, I think Ace, you have a point--

176
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,888
Ma, I'm sorry, but at this point,

177
00:09:14,972 --> 00:09:17,224
I'm not listening
to anything you have to say.

178
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,559
So please, don't interfere.

179
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:26,400
Why can't he see...

180
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:30,028
that I only did
what I did because I care?

181
00:09:31,405 --> 00:09:35,784
Why do I feel like it's always my fault?

182
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,286
It's so unfair.

183
00:09:42,332 --> 00:09:44,918
I think I need therapy too.

184
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:47,963
This is nothing new, Katarina.

185
00:09:48,046 --> 00:09:50,757
You always want your will imposed.

186
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:53,218
But guess what?

187
00:09:54,136 --> 00:09:55,887
You never win against me.

188
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:58,265
Aren't you exhausted?

189
00:10:00,726 --> 00:10:01,727
Why?

190
00:10:03,562 --> 00:10:04,938
Are you?

191
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:09,276
Are you exhausted, Divino?

192
00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:15,073
What do you want to do?

193
00:10:17,242 --> 00:10:18,535
You want us to separate?

194
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:23,915
Do you really want me to answer that?

195
00:10:23,999 --> 00:10:25,167
Yes.

196
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:27,085
Answer it.

197
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:49,816
I've read the police report.

198
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:52,402
How are you feeling now?

199
00:10:52,486 --> 00:10:54,154
Fine, sir.

200
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,742
How are you and Ma'am Gem?

201
00:11:05,874 --> 00:11:07,709
Well, she's still in the hospital,

202
00:11:07,793 --> 00:11:09,336
but she's doing okay.

203
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:10,504
Healing.

204
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:12,547
Thank you for your concern.

205
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:15,425
I'm sorry, sir,
I wasn't able to protect you.

206
00:11:15,926 --> 00:11:18,428
It was so sudden
that I was caught off guard.

207
00:11:19,054 --> 00:11:21,556
By the way,
thank you for paying the hospital bill

208
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:24,518
and for sending security personnel
to guard our house.

209
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:28,271
But you can tell them to stop now.

210
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:31,149
We don't want to cause you
any more inconvenience.

211
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:34,736
All right.

212
00:11:35,404 --> 00:11:38,156
Anyway,
are you ready to get back to work?

213
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:40,325
Yes, sir.

214
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:51,878
Come on! Faster!

215
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:21,908
Good job!

216
00:12:21,992 --> 00:12:23,034
Water break!

217
00:12:34,004 --> 00:12:34,921
That was amazing, sir.

218
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:48,393
Oh, okay. Last drill.

219
00:12:48,477 --> 00:12:50,228
Close-combat sparring.

220
00:12:50,312 --> 00:12:52,397
Teo, come here!

221
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:56,610
- Sir?
- Be my sparring partner.

222
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:09,039
Sir, please stop.

223
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:10,373
Huh?

224
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,251
You want me to stop?

225
00:13:16,338 --> 00:13:17,672
I was even holding back.

226
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:26,681
Thank you.

227
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:28,683
Hello?

228
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:29,643
Teo.

229
00:13:30,644 --> 00:13:32,938
Teo, Papa has been discharged
from the hospital.

230
00:13:33,021 --> 00:13:34,564
Thanks for your help.

231
00:13:34,648 --> 00:13:36,775
Thank you, Jepoy.

232
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:38,193
Sorry for the trouble.

233
00:13:38,276 --> 00:13:40,612
There was no one else
I could ask for help.

234
00:13:40,695 --> 00:13:42,531
Are you sure no one followed you and Lisa?

235
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:44,115
Yes, I'm sure.

236
00:13:44,199 --> 00:13:46,034
I asked her aunt how she's been doing.

237
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:47,994
She's still in shock from what happened.

238
00:13:48,078 --> 00:13:51,414
They're planning to move to Surigao.

239
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:54,584
Maybe it's all for the best
that they move far away from here.

240
00:13:54,668 --> 00:13:57,003
Don't you want to move far away too?

241
00:13:57,087 --> 00:13:59,756
Somewhere even Yana's shadow can't reach.

242
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,926
Maybe fate brought us back together
because we have unfinished business.

243
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:05,178
That's if it doesn't end you first.

244
00:14:05,262 --> 00:14:07,097
I'm not afraid, Jepoy.

245
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:10,183
<i>If that really was my fate,</i>

246
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:12,519
my life should've ended long ago.

247
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:16,648
There's a reason I'm still here today.

248
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:18,066
I guess you're right, Teo.

249
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:20,819
If you need anything, just let me know.

250
00:14:21,695 --> 00:14:24,197
I might be able to help in some way.

251
00:14:24,823 --> 00:14:26,157
Thank you, Jepoy.

252
00:14:26,241 --> 00:14:27,742
All right. Thanks again.

253
00:14:27,826 --> 00:14:29,411
- Take care.
- You too.

254
00:14:42,173 --> 00:14:44,217
- Good morning, Judge.
- Oh, Alonzo.

255
00:14:44,301 --> 00:14:45,427
Well...

256
00:14:46,636 --> 00:14:48,221
I just wanted to settle some of my debt.

257
00:14:48,305 --> 00:14:51,725
I'm sorry if this is
all I can pay you back for now,

258
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:54,060
even though I've just received my salary.

259
00:14:54,144 --> 00:14:56,438
Alonzo, I'm not in a hurry to get it back.

260
00:14:56,521 --> 00:15:00,358
I know that, sir, but debt is still debt.

261
00:15:00,442 --> 00:15:02,152
No matter how small the amount,

262
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,779
what matters is I keep my word
to pay you back

263
00:15:04,863 --> 00:15:05,989
on the day I promised.

264
00:15:06,072 --> 00:15:07,324
That's true.

265
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,326
You know, to be honest,

266
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:12,120
I appreciate people like you
who keep their word.

267
00:15:12,621 --> 00:15:13,955
Thank you, Judge.

268
00:15:14,039 --> 00:15:15,373
Anyway, I'll head to the garage now.

269
00:15:23,506 --> 00:15:24,633
Sir.

270
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:26,593
What do you think?

271
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:28,803
We didn't notice anything suspicious.

272
00:15:28,887 --> 00:15:30,930
They rarely even left the house.

273
00:15:31,014 --> 00:15:32,349
Are you sure?

274
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:33,433
Yes, sir.

275
00:15:33,516 --> 00:15:35,018
I kept watch in front of their house.

276
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:37,228
There was no other exit.

277
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:38,813
Every time he'd leave,

278
00:15:38,897 --> 00:15:41,691
I made sure to inform you,
just like we agreed.

279
00:15:41,775 --> 00:15:43,693
Do you want me to keep watching them?

280
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:45,945
No.

281
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,076
Welcome home, Gem.

282
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:52,535
Thank you, Raya.

283
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:54,204
You're now safe, love,

284
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:56,331
in our home and with me.

285
00:15:56,414 --> 00:15:58,291
Welcome back, Gem.

286
00:15:58,375 --> 00:15:59,668
Thank you, Mama.

287
00:15:59,751 --> 00:16:01,252
Welcome home, Gem.

288
00:16:01,336 --> 00:16:02,671
Thank you, Papa.

289
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:05,840
Ma'am Gem...

290
00:16:05,924 --> 00:16:08,218
Did you know that Mabel prayed really hard

291
00:16:08,301 --> 00:16:10,929
just so you could escape
from your kidnapper?

292
00:16:11,012 --> 00:16:12,347
That's true, Ma'am Gem.

293
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,640
But it wasn't just me.

294
00:16:13,723 --> 00:16:15,433
All my relatives prayed hard for you too.

295
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:18,353
We missed you here, ma'am.

296
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:21,773
We didn't have
our beautiful and kind princess.

297
00:16:21,856 --> 00:16:25,110
By the way, ma'am,
we have something for you.

298
00:16:27,237 --> 00:16:29,823
It can help drive away bad spirits,

299
00:16:29,906 --> 00:16:31,157
which are abundant here.

300
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,664
Miss Rica, thank you.

301
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,582
I'll always have this with me.

302
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,501
Welcome back, ma'am.

303
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,843
Hello, Papa.

304
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:51,177
<i>Gem, my love.</i>

305
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:53,179
I was about to fly to Manila.

306
00:16:53,263 --> 00:16:56,307
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>I wasn't there to protect you.</i>

307
00:16:56,391 --> 00:16:59,602
I prayed every day for your safety.

308
00:16:59,686 --> 00:17:01,020
I'm okay, Papa.

309
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:03,398
Maybe I'll visit you next month.

310
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:05,483
- See you.
- All right.

311
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:08,069
What's that noise? What's happening?

312
00:17:08,778 --> 00:17:10,613
We just have a small celebration

313
00:17:10,697 --> 00:17:12,949
to celebrate our safe return.

314
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,409
Wow, amazing.

315
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:16,619
She even has a Spanish father.

316
00:17:18,163 --> 00:17:19,831
She's really an expert con artist.

317
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:25,003
Yes, Papa.
Thank you. I love you.

318
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:32,802
Don't show them that you're sad,

319
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:34,387
or you might blow your cover.

320
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:37,640
You should be sweet to me.

321
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:41,561
Ma'am Gem's efforts will be in vain
if you get caught.

322
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:44,898
Come on, don't be shy.

323
00:17:44,981 --> 00:17:46,733
This is for you, okay?

324
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:51,488
Ace.

325
00:17:59,788 --> 00:18:03,708
That's also one of the reasons
why I don't trust your driver.

326
00:18:05,210 --> 00:18:08,546
Something's going on
between him and Larajean.

327
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,840
Why does it seem so sudden?

328
00:18:11,382 --> 00:18:12,550
Oh, well...

329
00:18:12,634 --> 00:18:15,678
I have enough stress already
to even tell your mom.

330
00:18:15,762 --> 00:18:17,430
For now, we celebrate.

331
00:18:40,787 --> 00:18:41,955
Thank you.

332
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:54,175
Good evening, ma'am.

333
00:18:54,259 --> 00:18:55,426
Good evening.

334
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:06,020
Gem.

335
00:19:09,858 --> 00:19:10,775
Can we talk?

336
00:19:12,402 --> 00:19:13,486
Yeah.

337
00:19:16,531 --> 00:19:18,074
Gem, I...

338
00:19:20,285 --> 00:19:21,494
I...

339
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:25,373
I'm...

340
00:19:25,456 --> 00:19:27,208
Papa and Ace already know...

341
00:19:29,836 --> 00:19:31,963
that it was your men who shot me.

342
00:19:32,630 --> 00:19:33,923
Yes.

343
00:19:34,007 --> 00:19:35,258
And you're fine with it?

344
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:37,594
They're fine with it.

345
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:40,013
Am I fine with it?

346
00:19:40,096 --> 00:19:43,182
If I feel like I badly need justice,
then I might...

347
00:19:43,266 --> 00:19:46,686
Gem,
whatever it is that you want,

348
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:47,937
tell me.

349
00:19:48,646 --> 00:19:50,481
I'll give it to you.

350
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:53,902
I might not.

351
00:20:00,658 --> 00:20:01,993
Thank you.

352
00:20:02,076 --> 00:20:03,745
- I'm sorry.
- Can I...

353
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:05,455
join you guys?

354
00:20:36,945 --> 00:20:39,489
Mm, I told you.

355
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:41,240
Come on.

356
00:20:45,453 --> 00:20:48,373
Aw, it's all right.

357
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:50,249
Okay?

358
00:21:32,542 --> 00:21:35,169
Love, can you get me
a towel, please?

359
00:21:36,129 --> 00:21:37,255
Coming.

360
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:47,473
Here you go.

361
00:21:50,435 --> 00:21:51,477
Join me?

362
00:21:51,561 --> 00:21:53,062
It still hurts.

363
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:56,774
Maybe soon?

364
00:22:24,469 --> 00:22:25,678
Pa.

365
00:22:27,013 --> 00:22:28,181
Hey.

366
00:22:28,848 --> 00:22:30,183
You don't look satisfied.

367
00:22:31,309 --> 00:22:32,477
How was the party?

368
00:22:37,148 --> 00:22:38,399
Son...

369
00:22:39,901 --> 00:22:41,110
By the way,

370
00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:44,072
I noticed earlier that someone's...

371
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:47,325
still watching our house.

372
00:22:47,408 --> 00:22:48,409
I thought they'd stop now.

373
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:50,536
Who is it?

374
00:22:57,877 --> 00:22:59,087
So, they're still there.

375
00:24:09,365 --> 00:24:10,700
Yes, Boss Khaled?

376
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:13,286
Find that Filipino boyfriend of Yana.

377
00:24:13,369 --> 00:24:15,413
His name is Mateo Crisanto.

378
00:24:15,496 --> 00:24:17,165
<i>He surely knows something.</i>

379
00:24:17,248 --> 00:24:18,958
Trace where the money is.

380
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:21,252
Okay, Boss Khaled.

381
00:24:40,563 --> 00:24:43,816
Where's the money you stole in Marrakech?

382
00:24:45,568 --> 00:24:47,153
I don't know what you're talking about.

383
00:24:48,446 --> 00:24:51,699
The money you and Chameleon ran away with.

384
00:24:52,533 --> 00:24:54,076
Khaled's looking for it.

385
00:24:55,828 --> 00:24:57,622
I don't have the money.

386
00:24:58,706 --> 00:25:00,708
I didn't even touch it.

387
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,563
Go ahead.

388
00:25:27,026 --> 00:25:29,779
I dare you to come closer.
Let's see how tough you are.

389
00:25:29,862 --> 00:25:31,906
Go ahead and shoot.

390
00:25:32,406 --> 00:25:34,867
You can't get anything from me,
because I don't have the money!

391
00:25:40,665 --> 00:25:43,417
Hey, hey, hey! What's going on here?

392
00:25:43,501 --> 00:25:45,169
Keep coming, I dare you.

393
00:25:45,253 --> 00:25:46,295
What's happening?

394
00:25:46,837 --> 00:25:47,838
Move!

395
00:25:58,432 --> 00:25:59,767
We should do this more often.

396
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:00,810
Thank you.

397
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:01,978
I agree, Mama.

398
00:26:03,187 --> 00:26:04,814
I know we're not that close.

399
00:26:05,439 --> 00:26:07,191
And I truly regret it.

400
00:26:07,275 --> 00:26:08,776
But let's face it.

401
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:12,363
My relationship with Ace
is not the same as yours.

402
00:26:13,531 --> 00:26:15,241
I'm just meddlesome sometimes.

403
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:19,036
Sadly, though, you became the victim.

404
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,872
But I learned my lesson.

405
00:26:22,790 --> 00:26:24,125
I shouldn't have done that.

406
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:27,837
It's okay, Mama.
If I was a mother,

407
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:30,214
I would have done the same thing.

408
00:26:31,007 --> 00:26:32,591
It was just an accident.

409
00:26:32,675 --> 00:26:33,884
You didn't want that to happen.

410
00:26:33,968 --> 00:26:35,386
But really...

411
00:26:36,721 --> 00:26:37,888
thank you for everything.

412
00:26:38,806 --> 00:26:40,808
For taking care of Ace,

413
00:26:40,891 --> 00:26:42,518
for being patient,

414
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:45,980
and most of all, for putting up with me.

415
00:26:46,063 --> 00:26:48,274
You know, if I were in your place,

416
00:26:48,357 --> 00:26:49,942
I would have left a long time ago.

417
00:26:54,989 --> 00:26:56,282
Actually, Mama...

418
00:26:57,658 --> 00:26:59,243
I want to leave.

419
00:27:00,911 --> 00:27:03,706
I just want
to take a break and relax

420
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:05,875
because everything
is just so traumatizing.

421
00:27:08,336 --> 00:27:11,339
And I hope you could help me convince Ace.

422
00:27:16,802 --> 00:27:18,262
I'll have one.

423
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:22,683
Hey, move a little bit. You're too close.

424
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:31,400
Oh, look!
Princess Raya has a bodyguard now.

425
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:32,610
Move over.

426
00:27:32,693 --> 00:27:35,571
You might get kidnapped or recruited.

427
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:36,947
What's with you?

428
00:27:37,031 --> 00:27:38,866
Should I bite your tongue
to make you shut up?

429
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:43,496
Girl, just tell me,
and I'll roast this bitch for you.

430
00:27:43,579 --> 00:27:45,414
No cap. I got you.

431
00:27:45,498 --> 00:27:46,957
Really?

432
00:27:47,041 --> 00:27:50,211
You didn't even bother
to come to my house.

433
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:51,337
At least Ronnie did.

434
00:27:54,090 --> 00:27:56,842
Ronnie! Hi!

435
00:27:58,219 --> 00:27:59,678
How are you?

436
00:27:59,762 --> 00:28:02,014
Ma'am, unauthorized approach.

437
00:28:02,556 --> 00:28:03,557
What?

438
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,684
I was the one who approached him.

439
00:28:05,768 --> 00:28:07,269
Why is it unauthorized?

440
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:08,854
Order of Mrs. Verona.

441
00:28:08,938 --> 00:28:10,898
No close contact unless cleared.

442
00:28:11,482 --> 00:28:13,317
It's okay.
I have to go to class anyway.

443
00:28:13,401 --> 00:28:14,527
I'll see you later.

444
00:28:15,194 --> 00:28:16,445
Okay.

445
00:28:22,952 --> 00:28:25,204
I thought you were friends.

446
00:28:25,287 --> 00:28:26,789
I thought so too.

447
00:28:27,957 --> 00:28:29,291
Raya, I'm really sorry.

448
00:28:29,375 --> 00:28:31,669
You know I'm just following Mom's orders.

449
00:28:31,752 --> 00:28:33,921
Please don't get mad at me.

450
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:35,631
It's okay. I understand.

451
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:38,384
I'm glad we're okay now.

452
00:28:38,843 --> 00:28:40,469
But Ronnie...

453
00:28:40,553 --> 00:28:43,097
Maybe he just feels intimidated by...

454
00:28:45,558 --> 00:28:47,059
- Whatever.
- Look at him.

455
00:28:54,233 --> 00:28:56,986
Ronnie, why aren't you
answering your phone?

456
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:58,654
It has been ringing nonstop.

457
00:29:07,872 --> 00:29:09,206
You're being nosy.

458
00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:11,208
Have you finished your assignment?

459
00:29:11,292 --> 00:29:13,377
Hmm... almost.

460
00:29:13,461 --> 00:29:14,962
Okay, I'll check it later.

461
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:16,672
- Finish it.
- Okay.

462
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:19,884
I'll tell on you to Teo.

463
00:29:20,801 --> 00:29:22,636
Tsk. How annoying.

464
00:29:25,181 --> 00:29:26,432
Ma.

465
00:29:26,515 --> 00:29:29,268
Can we talk about Mr. Ruben?

466
00:29:30,102 --> 00:29:31,437
He's kind of...

467
00:29:32,354 --> 00:29:33,647
weird.

468
00:29:33,731 --> 00:29:36,525
You need a bodyguard.
We all do.

469
00:29:36,609 --> 00:29:38,486
You have to live with it.

470
00:29:38,569 --> 00:29:41,447
Can he wait outside the school
or something?

471
00:29:41,530 --> 00:29:44,033
It's like I have
a big, bulky Siamese twin.

472
00:29:44,116 --> 00:29:47,453
Well, it's either that,
or you're home-schooled.

473
00:29:47,536 --> 00:29:49,121
You decide.
What do you want?

474
00:29:50,581 --> 00:29:52,416
Raya, we are targets.

475
00:29:52,500 --> 00:29:54,251
So we need to be careful.

476
00:29:54,335 --> 00:29:56,212
Have they identified the kidnappers?

477
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:59,381
No,
and that's why you have to cooperate.

478
00:29:59,465 --> 00:30:01,592
They're still in pursuit of them.

479
00:30:01,675 --> 00:30:04,345
The family can't afford another crisis.

480
00:30:08,766 --> 00:30:09,934
Get it?

481
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:15,481
- Mmm.
- Thank you.

482
00:30:15,564 --> 00:30:16,607
Wow!

483
00:30:17,149 --> 00:30:18,859
- This is good.
- Dessert time.

484
00:30:18,943 --> 00:30:22,279
Ooh! That looks good, Gem.

485
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:24,698
Your chocolate is so good.

486
00:30:24,782 --> 00:30:26,200
- I swear.
- Thank you.

487
00:30:26,283 --> 00:30:27,701
- Wow.
- Take a seat.

488
00:30:27,785 --> 00:30:29,119
I didn't know you baked.

489
00:30:29,203 --> 00:30:31,247
It's just my mama's old recipe.

490
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:33,165
It looks amazing, my love.

491
00:30:33,249 --> 00:30:34,917
This is special.

492
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,126
Is there an occasion?

493
00:30:36,210 --> 00:30:38,420
No, there's no occasion.

494
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:41,173
This is some kind of a...

495
00:30:41,257 --> 00:30:42,758
bribe, right, Gem?

496
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:44,760
Mama, it's not a bribe.

497
00:30:46,345 --> 00:30:49,890
But I was hoping if I could take a break.

498
00:30:49,974 --> 00:30:51,517
- Break?
- Mm-hmm.

499
00:30:51,600 --> 00:30:53,143
A break from all of this.

500
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:55,563
Some kind of a retreat.

501
00:30:56,063 --> 00:30:57,648
And I think it's a good idea.

502
00:30:57,731 --> 00:30:59,066
I'll go with you.

503
00:30:59,733 --> 00:31:01,110
Sure, love.

504
00:31:01,193 --> 00:31:02,236
But I know you're busy,

505
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:04,613
and I don't want to bother you.

506
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:07,116
That's why I was hoping
if I could do it by myself.

507
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:10,119
It's better than therapy.

508
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,499
Okay. I'll allow you to go.

509
00:31:15,583 --> 00:31:18,419
But take Miss Rica
and one of the bodyguards with you.

510
00:31:18,502 --> 00:31:21,005
If not, I'm sorry, but you can't go.

511
00:31:21,088 --> 00:31:24,550
I think it's a good deal.
Take it.

512
00:31:24,633 --> 00:31:27,761
Just bring Miss Rica.
She's not going to be your bodyguard.

513
00:31:27,845 --> 00:31:29,471
She'll be your chaperone.

514
00:31:29,555 --> 00:31:31,473
At least, you know,
she's going to fix your things,

515
00:31:31,557 --> 00:31:33,475
and she knows all of your quirks.

516
00:31:33,559 --> 00:31:34,768
So, go.

517
00:31:34,852 --> 00:31:36,186
Thank you, Mama.

518
00:31:37,313 --> 00:31:40,232
And love, sure. I'll take your bodyguard.

519
00:32:18,729 --> 00:32:19,938
Wow.

520
00:32:20,022 --> 00:32:21,482
It's so beautiful here,
Ma'am Gem.

521
00:32:22,274 --> 00:32:25,152
- Who owns this place?
- My friend.

522
00:32:25,235 --> 00:32:29,323
But they're in America now,
so only the caretaker is here.

523
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,702
I don't know
if they told him about us coming.

524
00:32:33,786 --> 00:32:35,996
Welcome to Villa Pacifico, ma'am.

525
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:38,540
Are you Ma'am Hanna's friend?

526
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:40,250
Yes.

527
00:32:40,334 --> 00:32:43,754
I'm Jojo,
the farm's caretaker.

528
00:32:44,254 --> 00:32:47,758
Ma'am Hanna told me
you're staying here for now.

529
00:32:47,841 --> 00:32:49,468
- Welcome!
- Thank you.

530
00:32:49,551 --> 00:32:51,929
You can leave us now.
Just come back later.

531
00:32:52,012 --> 00:32:53,263
All right, ma'am.

532
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:57,601
All right, I'll take you to the cottage.

533
00:32:59,937 --> 00:33:01,105
This way, ma'am.

534
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:07,194
Be careful.
Mind the gaps on the pavement.

535
00:33:22,418 --> 00:33:25,838
Ma'am,
if you need anything, just call me.

536
00:33:26,380 --> 00:33:28,799
I clean and do the maintenance work.

537
00:33:28,882 --> 00:33:31,844
- I'm also a cook!
- Okay, just tell Rica about it.

538
00:33:32,386 --> 00:33:35,139
All right.
Miss, I'll take you to your room.

539
00:33:35,222 --> 00:33:36,682
Okay.

540
00:33:46,650 --> 00:33:48,110
We'll go to the junkyard

541
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:50,028
where the kidnappers took us.

542
00:33:51,739 --> 00:33:52,740
Go.

543
00:33:55,242 --> 00:33:56,493
Okay, sir.

544
00:34:05,502 --> 00:34:07,004
Sir, what are we doing here?

545
00:34:07,504 --> 00:34:09,882
I'm looking for leads
on the bastards who kidnapped us.

546
00:34:09,965 --> 00:34:12,676
I'm sure the police have checked that.

547
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:32,821
What's the size of your feet?

548
00:34:33,822 --> 00:34:35,240
Nine and a half, sir.

549
00:34:38,494 --> 00:34:39,495
Are you sure?

550
00:34:40,204 --> 00:34:41,205
Yes, sir.

551
00:34:42,247 --> 00:34:43,248
Why?

552
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:51,233
What did you want to tell me?

553
00:35:52,776 --> 00:35:54,778
Leon is in the Philippines.

554
00:35:55,612 --> 00:35:58,282
He's looking for the money you took
before you jumped off the bridge.

555
00:35:58,365 --> 00:35:59,616
What?

556
00:36:00,617 --> 00:36:02,202
Come here.

557
00:36:03,036 --> 00:36:04,663
What did he tell you?

558
00:36:04,746 --> 00:36:05,998
He thought I had it.

559
00:36:06,081 --> 00:36:08,125
He's asking me
for the money he stole in Morocco.

560
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:10,210
That was a long time ago.

561
00:36:10,294 --> 00:36:11,378
No way.

562
00:36:11,461 --> 00:36:13,297
But he'll bother us for sure.

563
00:36:16,466 --> 00:36:17,759
The ransom money.

564
00:36:19,303 --> 00:36:20,554
We'll get some from it.

565
00:36:21,805 --> 00:36:24,266
But Teo, that's too easy.

566
00:36:24,975 --> 00:36:27,436
That dirty, greedy animal.

567
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:28,854
Let's just pay him.

568
00:36:29,479 --> 00:36:31,273
Then we can live peacefully.

569
00:36:32,983 --> 00:36:34,902
You know, that's my dream for you.

570
00:36:36,028 --> 00:36:37,404
For us.

571
00:36:40,574 --> 00:36:41,658
Come here.

572
00:36:46,455 --> 00:36:48,790
We managed to get you away before.

573
00:36:49,458 --> 00:36:51,209
We'll manage to do it again.

574
00:36:54,087 --> 00:36:55,422
Teo.

575
00:36:56,715 --> 00:36:59,259
If I were free from the Veronas,

576
00:37:01,345 --> 00:37:03,513
would you be able to endure not seeing me?

577
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:05,682
You know the answer.

578
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:07,851
For me,

579
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,812
as long as you're safe.

580
00:37:11,772 --> 00:37:12,981
For me,

581
00:37:13,690 --> 00:37:15,275
wherever we can be together.

582
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:19,279
We can't be separated again, Teo.

583
00:37:19,988 --> 00:37:23,492
And I can't live without you
by my side again.

584
00:39:32,579 --> 00:39:33,538
Khaled.

585
00:39:33,622 --> 00:39:34,956
Did you get my money?

586
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,541
Send it to me now.

587
00:39:36,625 --> 00:39:38,710
So I can pay for my new identity,

588
00:39:39,878 --> 00:39:43,090
my new passport, IDs, everything!

589
00:39:43,715 --> 00:39:45,383
No, I don't have the money.

590
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:49,471
What's taking too long? Stupid!

591
00:39:49,554 --> 00:39:50,722
Stupid?

592
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:55,227
Did you just call me stupid?

593
00:39:55,310 --> 00:39:56,770
You know what, Khaled?

594
00:39:56,853 --> 00:39:58,188
When I get that money,

595
00:39:58,271 --> 00:40:00,607
do you think
I'm going to go back to Morocco?

596
00:40:00,690 --> 00:40:01,817
No!

597
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:04,736
I will not send you anything! Nothing!

598
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:06,196
You're a traitor!

599
00:40:07,447 --> 00:40:09,157
And you have no money!

600
00:40:14,246 --> 00:40:17,582
EX-JUDGE VERONA PAYS 40-MILLION RANSOM
FOR SON AND DAUGHTER-IN-LAW!

601
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,882
<i>A monkey might be smart...</i>

602
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,927
<i>but Leon is wise.</i>

603
00:40:39,563 --> 00:40:41,565
Can we just go back to dreaming?

604
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:49,239
After this, we're back to reality.

605
00:40:50,866 --> 00:40:52,075
That this...

606
00:40:54,786 --> 00:40:55,954
us...

607
00:40:56,538 --> 00:40:58,123
we can't be together.

608
00:40:58,540 --> 00:41:00,167
It's wrong.

609
00:41:01,209 --> 00:41:02,460
It's risky.

610
00:41:05,589 --> 00:41:07,257
You'll only get in trouble.

611
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,843
I'm married.

612
00:41:13,638 --> 00:41:15,390
To a husband who beats you up,

613
00:41:17,225 --> 00:41:18,935
who hurts you.

614
00:41:19,019 --> 00:41:21,188
A husband you don't even love.

615
00:41:24,191 --> 00:41:26,860
I should've chosen
to be with you in Morocco.

616
00:41:28,570 --> 00:41:30,906
I should not have chosen a new life.

617
00:41:33,366 --> 00:41:34,743
Don't worry.

618
00:41:34,826 --> 00:41:37,204
A brand-new life still awaits you.

619
00:41:39,039 --> 00:41:40,165
For us.

620
00:41:41,541 --> 00:41:43,126
A life together.

621
00:41:44,252 --> 00:41:45,837
I want that too, Teo.

622
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:51,635
But how?

623
00:41:56,890 --> 00:41:58,725
I'm married...

624
00:41:58,808 --> 00:42:00,936
and to a Verona.

625
00:42:01,478 --> 00:42:03,313
You know the truth.

626
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:07,025
They're illegal recruiters.

627
00:42:08,276 --> 00:42:11,446
They're smuggling precious gems and gold.

628
00:42:11,988 --> 00:42:14,699
And they bury whoever crosses them.

629
00:42:18,912 --> 00:42:20,747
That's what the Veronas do.

630
00:42:21,581 --> 00:42:23,124
Powerful,

631
00:42:23,875 --> 00:42:24,960
ruthless,

632
00:42:25,794 --> 00:42:27,045
insane.

633
00:42:30,674 --> 00:42:33,093
It's not easy to escape from them.

634
00:42:35,303 --> 00:42:36,429
Gem.

635
00:42:37,597 --> 00:42:39,975
All things impossible...

636
00:42:40,684 --> 00:42:42,852
can be made possible.

637
00:42:43,186 --> 00:42:45,188
You just have to be brave

638
00:42:45,772 --> 00:42:47,565
and never give up.

639
00:42:47,941 --> 00:42:51,611
As long as we have each other
and fight side by side.

640
00:42:52,404 --> 00:42:55,031
We can't let fear imprison us.

641
00:42:55,782 --> 00:42:57,367
We will try,

642
00:42:58,034 --> 00:43:01,538
and we will keep trying
with everything we have.

643
00:43:03,665 --> 00:43:05,834
Our lives are on the line here.

644
00:43:06,418 --> 00:43:08,169
Gem, you are not alone.

645
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,672
I'm with you.

646
00:43:12,424 --> 00:43:17,053
And I'll do everything I can
until the day you gain your freedom.

647
00:43:52,672 --> 00:43:54,007
Ma'am Gem!

648
00:43:54,090 --> 00:43:55,717
Yes, Rica?

649
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,177
Where have you been?

650
00:43:57,260 --> 00:43:58,470
I just went out for a walk.

651
00:43:58,553 --> 00:43:59,679
Ah.

652
00:44:01,723 --> 00:44:03,224
Good morning, Ma'am Gem.

653
00:44:04,684 --> 00:44:06,686
You're up early for some exercise.

654
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:09,981
I noticed you along the trail,
doing several laps.

655
00:44:13,485 --> 00:44:15,403
The air is fresh here.

656
00:44:16,321 --> 00:44:18,323
We don't have anything like this
back home.

657
00:44:18,406 --> 00:44:20,075
Perfect, I've got eggs with me.

658
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:21,868
I'll cook them for you.

659
00:44:21,951 --> 00:44:24,621
You must be exhausted.

660
00:44:45,809 --> 00:44:46,976
Ma'am Gem?

661
00:44:48,353 --> 00:44:49,938
Are you okay?

662
00:44:50,855 --> 00:44:52,690
I think I upset my stomach.

663
00:44:52,774 --> 00:44:54,401
Would you like some hot chocolate, ma'am?

664
00:44:54,984 --> 00:44:56,403
Yes, please. Thank you.

665
00:44:56,486 --> 00:44:58,488
All right, let me fix you a cup.
I'll be quick.

666
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:17,382
Thanks, boss. Take care.

667
00:45:23,304 --> 00:45:24,347
Ronnie.

668
00:45:24,973 --> 00:45:27,809
Why don't you answer this?
It's been ringing nonstop.

669
00:45:36,693 --> 00:45:39,195
It's... Raya.

670
00:45:40,405 --> 00:45:42,824
I'm trying to avoid her,
or I might blurt out everything I know.

671
00:45:43,533 --> 00:45:45,952
I'm sorry, Ronnie.

672
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:50,540
For telling you.
Now you're stuck carrying a secret.

673
00:45:50,623 --> 00:45:52,625
Tsk. It's okay. Come on.

674
00:45:52,709 --> 00:45:54,586
We're brothers, remember?

675
00:45:54,669 --> 00:45:56,087
We stick together.

676
00:45:56,588 --> 00:45:58,673
We're not related by blood,
but you're still family.

677
00:45:58,756 --> 00:45:59,757
So I've got your back.

678
00:46:02,260 --> 00:46:05,680
If you told me to stay away from Raya,

679
00:46:05,763 --> 00:46:09,100
I'd say the same thing to you about Gem.

680
00:46:29,871 --> 00:46:32,165
What's this? Room service?

681
00:46:32,248 --> 00:46:33,917
Eggs for you, madam.

682
00:46:34,584 --> 00:46:39,005
That workout must have worn you out,
so I made eggs for you.

683
00:46:39,088 --> 00:46:41,049
Go on, eat. You don't want to...

684
00:46:41,132 --> 00:46:42,759
Your smile looks different.

685
00:46:54,229 --> 00:46:57,649
So why were you and Teo
in the hut for so long?

686
00:46:58,691 --> 00:47:00,235
What did you guys do?

687
00:47:00,318 --> 00:47:01,903
It's none of your business.

688
00:47:02,445 --> 00:47:04,197
And don't expect me to spill the details.

689
00:47:04,822 --> 00:47:07,408
There we go. Lucky you.

690
00:47:08,368 --> 00:47:10,620
Of course I don't want to hear all that.

691
00:47:11,496 --> 00:47:12,747
Just tell me,

692
00:47:13,665 --> 00:47:15,416
what did you two talk about?

693
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:19,212
Hey, what were you guys talking about?

694
00:47:22,632 --> 00:47:23,716
Leon.

695
00:47:24,884 --> 00:47:27,554
- Leon?
- He's here.

696
00:47:27,637 --> 00:47:29,973
- What?
- He's looking for the money.

697
00:47:30,056 --> 00:47:31,766
That bald guy is actually here?

698
00:47:31,849 --> 00:47:34,477
That asshole would really travel
to the ends of the earth

699
00:47:34,561 --> 00:47:36,688
just for a payday, wouldn't he?
That was a long time ago.

700
00:47:36,771 --> 00:47:40,191
Khaled's orders. Shameless, right?

701
00:47:40,275 --> 00:47:43,528
If it were up to me,
I'd take him out.

702
00:47:44,153 --> 00:47:47,282
Let's just give him some money...
from the ransom.

703
00:47:47,365 --> 00:47:48,449
What do you mean?

704
00:47:48,533 --> 00:47:50,285
Are you actually
going to give that jerk a cut?

705
00:47:50,368 --> 00:47:52,453
Gem, we literally
risked our lives for this.

706
00:47:52,537 --> 00:47:55,665
- And he just gets to enjoy it?
- I know!

707
00:47:56,791 --> 00:47:58,334
We don't have a choice.

708
00:47:58,418 --> 00:48:00,712
- What do you mean, no choice?
- It's better than things getting messy.

709
00:48:03,256 --> 00:48:04,841
Whatever.

710
00:48:18,438 --> 00:48:21,274
Attorney, Mr. Domingo is here.

711
00:48:24,068 --> 00:48:25,820
Sir, I'll just reschedule.

712
00:48:25,903 --> 00:48:27,864
No, I'll be there,
just give me a minute.

713
00:48:33,494 --> 00:48:35,330
I said give me a minute!

714
00:49:21,709 --> 00:49:23,628
By the way,
I talked to Gimo.

715
00:49:24,212 --> 00:49:25,797
He already took his share.

716
00:49:26,714 --> 00:49:30,510
I'll follow suit. And after that...

717
00:49:30,593 --> 00:49:33,346
we'll get our escape plan sorted out.

718
00:49:38,059 --> 00:49:41,479
- Ours?
- Mm. You don't want to?

719
00:49:42,730 --> 00:49:44,482
Of course I do.

720
00:49:45,900 --> 00:49:47,568
But what about your family?

721
00:49:51,364 --> 00:49:54,450
My dad still owes his friend some money.

722
00:49:54,534 --> 00:49:57,829
Then let's pay it off.
Take it from the ransom.

723
00:49:58,413 --> 00:49:59,330
No.

724
00:49:59,414 --> 00:50:02,792
They'll wonder
where he got that kind of cash.

725
00:50:02,875 --> 00:50:05,211
Then we pay it back in installments,

726
00:50:05,294 --> 00:50:06,713
like 5,000 at a time.

727
00:50:07,588 --> 00:50:09,549
Mm. Seems solid, right?

728
00:50:13,177 --> 00:50:14,595
Just wait a little longer.

729
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:17,181
The plan is in motion.

730
00:50:19,934 --> 00:50:21,185
This is it.

731
00:50:23,062 --> 00:50:26,649
- No turning back?
- No turning back.

732
00:50:48,379 --> 00:50:50,173
I knew it.

733
00:50:50,256 --> 00:50:51,883
You're not gay.

734
00:50:56,721 --> 00:50:57,805
Let me go.

735
00:51:01,184 --> 00:51:03,019
Are you having an affair with my wife?

736
00:51:03,686 --> 00:51:04,854
Answer me!

737
00:51:06,689 --> 00:51:08,274
Let me go.

738
00:51:17,658 --> 00:51:18,951
Let me go.

739
00:51:30,171 --> 00:51:31,631
Just admit it.

740
00:51:41,682 --> 00:51:43,518
Let me out of here.

741
00:51:55,613 --> 00:51:56,739
Shit!

742
00:51:58,574 --> 00:51:59,909
Who are you with?

743
00:52:17,301 --> 00:52:18,469
<i>Hello?</i>

744
00:52:19,887 --> 00:52:20,888
Hello?

745
00:52:24,809 --> 00:52:25,893
Hello?

746
00:52:50,668 --> 00:52:53,838
Teo, this isn't like Gimo.

747
00:52:55,047 --> 00:52:56,716
I'm worried about him.

748
00:52:57,633 --> 00:52:59,635
Same here, he's been gone all day.

749
00:52:59,719 --> 00:53:01,596
Do you think he ran off with the money?

750
00:53:01,679 --> 00:53:03,723
Teo, Gimo isn't that kind of person.

751
00:53:04,974 --> 00:53:06,767
I'm heading to the city.
I know where he lives.

752
00:53:07,351 --> 00:53:09,437
I'll meet you there. I'm coming with you.

753
00:53:33,836 --> 00:53:35,004
Ace.

754
00:53:40,635 --> 00:53:44,055
How's my beautiful wife? Surprise.

755
00:54:01,405 --> 00:54:02,406
Gem?

756
00:54:30,101 --> 00:54:31,185
Gem?

757
00:54:35,564 --> 00:54:36,983
I had my doubts...

758
00:54:37,566 --> 00:54:39,568
You're dead, you bastard!

759
00:54:50,454 --> 00:54:51,622
S-Sir...

760
00:54:52,540 --> 00:54:54,458
Sir, I'm telling the truth.

761
00:54:58,254 --> 00:55:00,506
- Sir.
- Your lover is here.

762
00:55:04,218 --> 00:55:05,386
Ma'am.

763
00:55:06,971 --> 00:55:08,222
That's enough.

764
00:55:09,098 --> 00:55:12,435
You filthy disgusting son of a bitch.

765
00:55:13,269 --> 00:55:14,687
What are you doing here?

766
00:55:16,022 --> 00:55:17,773
Were you meeting my wife?

767
00:55:18,274 --> 00:55:19,775
- No, sir.
- No!

768
00:55:19,859 --> 00:55:21,819
I really thought
Ma'am Gem wanted me to pick her up,

769
00:55:21,902 --> 00:55:23,404
- that's why I came here.
- And you?

770
00:55:23,487 --> 00:55:24,739
What is he to you?

771
00:55:25,281 --> 00:55:26,782
Ace... nothing.

772
00:55:26,866 --> 00:55:28,743
One guy isn't enough for you, is it?

773
00:55:28,826 --> 00:55:30,745
What are you talking about?

774
00:55:30,828 --> 00:55:34,248
That's not true. It's only you.

775
00:55:35,124 --> 00:55:37,084
Bring Gem's other man in here.

776
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:41,088
Ace, knock it off. Drop it.

777
00:55:41,589 --> 00:55:43,841
Quit doing this. It's not true.

778
00:55:43,924 --> 00:55:45,801
Just admit it already.

779
00:55:45,885 --> 00:55:48,345
There's nothing to admit
because it's not true!

780
00:55:55,061 --> 00:55:57,813
Give it a rest. That's enough.

781
00:56:09,408 --> 00:56:10,826
You're not going to talk?

782
00:56:10,910 --> 00:56:12,661
Ace, please.

783
00:56:12,745 --> 00:56:15,164
Ace, I'm begging you...

784
00:56:15,664 --> 00:56:17,083
Cut it out.

785
00:56:18,417 --> 00:56:19,794
Please, stop.

786
00:56:26,634 --> 00:56:28,469
Go after her!

787
00:56:29,095 --> 00:56:30,179
Hurry!

788
00:56:38,521 --> 00:56:39,563
Gimo.

789
00:56:43,526 --> 00:56:45,319
I'll come back for you, okay?

790
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:46,570
I'll be back, Gimo.

791
00:56:52,868 --> 00:56:53,786
Yes, Rica?

792
00:56:53,869 --> 00:56:54,995
<i>Hello, Judge?</i>

793
00:56:55,079 --> 00:56:56,872
It's a mess over here!

794
00:56:56,956 --> 00:56:59,041
<i>Sir Ace is here!</i>

795
00:56:59,125 --> 00:57:02,336
He's out to kill Ma'am Gem and Teo!

796
00:57:02,419 --> 00:57:05,172
And the caretaker too!

797
00:57:05,798 --> 00:57:06,799
Stay put.

798
00:57:07,716 --> 00:57:10,845
Don't go anywhere.
Wait for us there.

799
00:57:10,928 --> 00:57:12,471
Yes, Judge.

800
00:57:15,766 --> 00:57:16,892
What's going on?

801
00:57:37,496 --> 00:57:39,331
Where do you think you're going?

802
00:57:45,504 --> 00:57:48,132
Ace, I'm begging you.
Stop this.

803
00:57:48,215 --> 00:57:49,633
Where, huh?

804
00:57:51,677 --> 00:57:53,512
You think you can escape from me?

805
00:58:13,324 --> 00:58:15,409
You think you can run away from me?

806
00:58:16,702 --> 00:58:20,372
I don't chase my corner.

807
00:58:21,749 --> 00:58:23,751
You're all exactly where I want you to be.

808
00:58:25,669 --> 00:58:26,921
Stop it!

809
00:58:27,588 --> 00:58:28,631
Ace!

810
00:58:31,634 --> 00:58:32,676
Pick him up!

811
00:58:45,689 --> 00:58:47,024
<i>This will be your grave.</i>

812
00:58:47,107 --> 00:58:48,567
- Ace, no!
- No! Don't do it!

813
00:58:49,276 --> 00:58:53,447
I'm pregnant! Don't you care
if you hurt me and your child?

814
00:58:53,530 --> 00:58:54,865
My child? Are you sure about that?

815
00:58:54,949 --> 00:58:57,952
We'll undergo a paternity test.
What if it isn't yours?

816
00:58:58,035 --> 00:58:59,995
Nothing will change.
We'll get out of here.

817
00:59:00,079 --> 00:59:02,665
<i>I want everyone to know</i>
<i>that I was almost shot to death</i>

818
00:59:02,748 --> 00:59:03,958
<i>by Attorney Ace Verona.</i>

819
00:59:04,041 --> 00:59:05,960
It's your word against ours.

820
00:59:06,043 --> 00:59:08,837
<i>And our word</i>
<i>is more powerful than yours.</i>

821
00:59:08,921 --> 00:59:10,673
This is Yana. We got caught.

822
00:59:10,756 --> 00:59:12,508
<i>Boss, please help us.</i>

823
00:59:12,591 --> 00:59:13,425
Boss!
